      "id": 14,
      "options": {
        "content": "### Receiver budget policy\n\n- **degraded** means the receiver stayed active but was downswitched to a cheaper useful encoding.\n- **paused** means the subscription still exists, but room policy withheld a whole route to stay within budget.\n- **resumed** means a policy-paused route was allowed back after stable budget recovery.\n- **protected_over_budget** means pinned, featured, readable-detail or active-speaker room policy intentionally won over the current BWE estimate.\n\nOpen **Room Graph** or the diagnostics user lookup to inspect the exact receiver BWE, selected budget, active route count, selected bitrate, pause reason, and exception reason.",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "title": "How to Read Receiver Budget Policy",
      "type": "text"
